h2.heading.heading--secondary#enhanced Basic Dropdown

p.paragraph.
  The dropdown is used for a single selection out of a list. 

.example
  .example__header
    .example__device-selection
      a.example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--mobile
      a.example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--tablet
      a.example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--desktop.is-active
  .example__content
    .dropdown(data-dropdown)
      .dropdown__label
      select.dropdown__select
        option Schweiz
        option Regenbogenland

.toggle
  .toggle__button.icon.icon--source See code
  .toggle__content
    .tab-panel
      .tab-panel__header
        .tab-panel__header__tab HTML
      .tab-panel__content
        .tab-panel__content__tab.is-active
          .tab-panel__content__tab__fullwidth-content
            .highlight: pre.highlight__listing.hljs: code.js
              :highlight
                <div data-dropdown="data-dropdown" class="dropdown">
                  <div class="dropdown__label"></div>
                  <select class="dropdown__select">
                    <option>Schweiz</option>
                    <option>Regenbogenland</option>
                  </select>
                </div>

h3.heading.heading--tertiary UX Checklist

ul.checklist
  li.checklist__item 
    :markdown
      Generally, if you have less than 5 options, a [segmented control](/components/form-and-imput-elements/segmented-control.html) might be the better option.
  li.checklist__item On mobile devices, use native dropdown pickers.

